it.polito.dp2.NFFG

Interface LinkReader

  • All Superinterfaces:
    NamedEntityReader

    public interface LinkReader
extends NamedEntityReader
    An interface for accessing information about the existing connections between two network nodes. A link represents a network connection that exists between two network nodes. It is defined as an oriented arc from a source node to a destination node. It is characterized by a name, which uniquely identifies it in the NF-FG, and the names of the source and destination nodes.
